  "description": "The Court is a superior court of record and a court of law and equity. It sits in all capital cities and elsewhere in Australia from time to time.<br />\n<br />\nThe primary functions of the Court are to, decide disputes according to law - promptly, courteously and effectively and, in so doing, to interpret the statutory law and develop the general law of the Commonwealth, so as to fulfil the role of a court exercising the judicial power of the Commonwealth under the Constitution.",
